heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 16.2mm per hour (ranked 4th in our records).  The storm lasted 5.3 hours and 9.2mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: The record duration for continuous rain was set on 04 January 2025, the storm lasted 37.2 hours with a total precipitation of 36.8mm and it reached 4.6mm per hour at times.

summary.description:

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 652 m), rainfall (down 0.1 mm), and light levels (up 4993 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1249 m), light levels (up 6946 lux), and rainfall (down 0.5 mm) when compared to today.
